The bolt can be locked in the rear position by the operating handle. The main safety is of protected push bolt type disconnecting the trigger bar and interlocking the hammer and sear. By rotating the barrel upwards and back, the SUB-2000 can be reduced to a size of 16" x 7" to facilitate secure storage and utilize the internal deployment lock which is operated by a proprietary key. Again, as per customer request, Buffalo Bore has developed two new 35 Whelen loads. Item 42A features a Sierra 225gr. SPTZ-BT bullet @ 2705 fps out of my Remington 700. You can use this TSX load for bad angle (quartering or going straight away) shots on the largest North American big game.

This ammo is designed to be the highest quality, most powerful/versatile, 35 Whelen ammo, in the world. It exhibits sub MOA accuracy in our test rifle.

title: For Trade:  Trade for AR15
postcontent:
This is the ultimate Home Defense combat shotgun. It is built on a Remington 870.

The nation's leading defender. For a half century the Remington Model 870 has been the pump shotgun of choice for government agencies. With over 10 million produced to date, it remains the standard by which all pump actions are measured. Its dual, non-binding action bars deliver ultra-smooth, reliable cycling. The ultimate pump shotgun, the Model 870 stands the test of time, extreme conditions and duty.
•Non-binding twin action bars provide smoothest/surest pump operation
•Receiver milled from solid block of steel
•3" chamber accepts all 2 ¾" and 3" 12-gauge shells
•Steel-lined/grooved fore-end for a stronger grip
•Breech block locks into barrel extension for strength and consistent head space
•Balanced sear and inertia firing pin prevents discharge unless action is closed and trigger is pulled
•Flexitab feeding system prevents a misfeed from jamming the shotgun
•Cross-bolt safety

The Modifications to the firearm are as follows.

It has a Knoxx Specops stock on it. It is adjustable to fit any person or can accommodate body armor. This is NOT a cheap stock like an ATI. This is meant for serious duty use.

The forend is a Surefire Remington 870 Weaponlight. This light is blindingly bright and great to easily identify anything that goes bump in the night. The forend alone retails for $300 dollars and they rarely come on the used market. It has buttons for continuous light and a pressure pad for momentary light.

The Firearm is coated in Ceracote H baked on finish. It is extremely durable and abrasive and chemical resistant. To have a long gun refinished in this coating runs about $200. The process is very labor intensive but results in the most durable firearm finish available and is well worth the money.

There is a single point sling mount between the stock and receiver for carrying the firearm with a single point sling but there are also mounts included to run a 2 point sling as well.

It has a side saddle on the side of the receiver that can hold 6 shotgun shells. This allows the firearm to have 13 rounds of ammunition carried on it before adding extra with your preferred method of carrying shells.

The magazine extension allows the firearm to have 7 shots including one in the chamber to allow for the most firepower before a reload possible. It functions reliably and is very heavy duty. The magazine spring is extra power to ensure that even under the most demanding conditions, the firearm will always reliably feed a new shell.

All of the internals were upgraded to new extreme duty police parts. This includes heavier springs for the hammer, shell lifter, and trigger sear and upgraded parts that are all machined and not MIM.

The barrel is an 18 inch factory Remington barrel with a cylinder bore. That means that the barrel has the optimal spread for close quarter combat and can fire any ammunition you put in it from birdshot to buckshot and slugs. It is the shortest barrel that can be legally fitted to the firearm. It can handle both 2 3/4" and 3" ammunition and has functioned flawlessly with both.

This is the ultimate combat shotgun and it is a shotgun you can trust your life to. I would not hesitate to grab this gun if I was having a home invasion. This shotgun will more than exceed your expectations for a shotgun and is the best that money can buy. All the parts and work for this shotgun total more than $1200.

title: For Sale:  SPRINGFIELD M6 SCOUT SURVIVAL RIFLE IN 22 LR / .410
postcontent: Up for sale is a late model Springfield M6 SCOUT Survival Rifle made in the USA. I have the barrel wrapped with 40 ft. of 550 Paracord and a sling with over 60 ft. of 550 Paracord. This is 22 LR over .410 shotgun in a break open/folding/or take apart format. Stock holds 15 rounds of 22 LR and 4 rounds of .410 2.5" or 3" shells. I have made the top of the front sight florescent orange so that it can be seen against a dark target. These rifles are getting very hard to come by and can cost upwards of $1200.00 They make the ultimate bug out / survival gun and when in take apart they only measure 18.5" long. The earlier versions of this rifle were made by the Czech Republic for Springfield. This is one of the last series made by Springfield USA as the "SCOUT" and has a trigger guard. It went out of production in the beginning of this century. It has the two scope mount holes. NOTE: On either side of the metal stock there is some light numbers that look to have been made with a hard graphite pencil by the Previous owner for some reason unbeknownst to me. Some Springfield M6 History: Springfield originally made the M6 for the Air Force B52 crew members in a 22 hornet / .410 with a 14 inch barrel. This is the civilian version of that gun. This is the last version of this design. The safety is on the hammer and there is a removable trigger guard. Both barrels are clean and clear of any imperfections with the 22 rifling clean & crisp. This rifle has been used very little in its lifetime. Rifle and shotgun are very accurate.
